{"key":"processedPost-12588213","value":{"id":12588213,"first":12581116,"last":12588229,"when":1274233544,"utime":"05/19/10 04:45 AM","cleanedPost":"Of course that's not the only way.&nbsp; I pasteurize straw for my farm in 55 gallon drums of water, heated with propane.&nbsp; For small quantities, using jars or spawn bags in a pot of hot/boiling water is MUCH faster than an oven and gets even pasteurization.&nbsp; Don't allow the temperature in the center of the substrate to exceed 160F during pasteurization, or keep it there longer than 90 minutes.&nbsp; The most common new grower mistake in pasteurizing is overheating, or past the correct time, which destroys beneficial microbes, giving molds the upper hand.<br />RR"}}